00:11:18,981 --> 00:11:21,022
And did that make me feel more comfortable?

250
00:11:21,022 --> 00:11:23,384
It's a powerful feeling that fashion gives.

251
00:11:23,384 --> 00:11:25,425
And dressing up a character helps you aspire

252
00:11:25,425 --> 00:11:26,726
to something personally.

253
00:11:26,726 --> 00:11:28,247
They give you a mission and incentive

254
00:11:28,247 --> 00:11:30,769
to explore that feeling off screen if you choose to.

255
00:11:32,091 --> 00:11:35,875
So the personal aspect of fashion can go terribly awry

256
00:11:35,875 --> 00:11:38,137
because it is so personal.

257
00:11:38,137 --> 00:11:39,859
Due to the cultural meaning,

258
00:11:39,859 --> 00:11:41,540
it's easy to mess it up sometimes,

259
00:11:41,540 --> 00:11:43,102
even more so because the industry

260
00:11:43,102 --> 00:11:44,884
doesn't talk about clothes much.

261
00:11:44,884 --> 00:11:47,146
So I don't necessarily think misuse of clothes

262
00:11:47,146 --> 00:11:49,668
comes from an ill-attentioned or harmful mindset,

263
00:11:49,668 --> 00:11:52,031
but if we're talking about why clothes matters,

264
00:11:52,031 --> 00:11:52,511
can't ignore it.

265
00:11:57,438 --> 00:11:57,959
Yeah.

266
00:11:57,959 --> 00:12:03,480
So of course I have to talk about sexualized fashion.

267
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:06,020
I've come to actually have very complicated feelings about it

268
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:09,321
by now, and I recommend reading Maddie Meyer's fantastic piece

269
00:12:09,321 --> 00:12:12,702
about the inexplicable sexiness of Ivy Valentine on Kotaku.

270
00:12:12,702 --> 00:12:15,803
As she writes, these outfits don't directly

271
00:12:15,803 --> 00:12:17,903
tell us anything about the characters wearing them.

272
00:12:17,903 --> 00:12:20,884
Sometimes they contradict the stories and personalities

273
00:12:20,884 --> 00:12:22,204
of the women in them.

274
00:12:22,204 --> 00:12:24,004
And this is true, and I'd love to see games move away

275
00:12:24,004 --> 00:12:24,845
from this.

276
00:12:25,477 --> 00:12:27,878
She does mention reclaiming sexiness for ourselves,

277
00:12:27,878 --> 00:12:32,579
though I find the problem with this is that it's hard to feel empowered when

278
00:12:32,579 --> 00:12:34,639
this is your option, or whatever else, right?

279
00:12:34,639 --> 00:12:39,581
It's clear when a male character gets a perfectly acceptable costume for

280
00:12:39,581 --> 00:12:43,722
the context they're in, while the female one is wearing the coverage equivalent of

281
00:12:43,722 --> 00:12:45,582
a band-aid, or a belt, I guess, in this case.

282
00:12:46,606 --> 00:12:48,946
To be clear, sexiness isn't inherently bad,

283
00:12:48,946 --> 00:12:52,367
but that doesn't mean it has to be used all the time,

284
00:12:52,367 --> 00:12:54,567
or that it has to be used at all, right?

285
00:12:54,567 --> 00:12:57,128
It doesn't mean a sexy outfit is the only way

286
00:12:57,128 --> 00:12:59,828
to show female empowerment.

287
00:12:59,828 --> 00:13:02,129
I'm glad you're liking those.

288
00:13:02,129 --> 00:13:05,710
It was a fun time looking them up.

289
00:13:05,710 --> 00:13:07,890
Okay, so that's kind of like the sexiness

290
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:09,990
in terms of like self-expression.

291
00:13:09,990 --> 00:13:12,731
But another thing that can go wrong

292
00:13:12,731 --> 00:13:16,091
is that I need you to first imagine this world with me.

293
00:13:16,949 --> 00:13:20,932
So this is another way fashion can be misused.

294
00:13:20,932 --> 00:13:23,354
Imagine with me a new world for a second

295
00:13:23,354 --> 00:13:25,936
where Americans are only ever shown wearing Cameo

296
00:13:25,936 --> 00:13:28,198
or the US flag in all forms of media.

297
00:13:28,198 --> 00:13:32,502
Fashion, TV, movies, games,

298
00:13:32,502 --> 00:13:34,083
you literally cannot do anything

299
00:13:34,083 --> 00:13:36,665
without seeing an American wearing the flag.

300
00:13:36,665 --> 00:13:38,366
And work through this with me.

301
00:13:38,366 --> 00:13:39,868
It sounds funny right now,

302
00:13:39,868 --> 00:13:42,049
but after years of depiction,

303
00:13:42,049 --> 00:13:45,272
how bored, how annoyed, how dumb would this eventually look?

304
00:13:46,090 --> 00:13:51,003
This is the simplest, most reductive way I can try to describe this and relate it to

305
00:13:51,003 --> 00:13:52,887
what I'm going to talk about.

306
00:13:52,887 --> 00:13:54,993
Clothes reflect culture and significance.

307
00:13:55,553 --> 00:14:00,375
Issues of cultural appropriation go far beyond the games industry and diversity,

308
00:14:00,375 --> 00:14:02,916
but that doesn't mean we can't make a difference.

309
00:14:02,916 --> 00:14:06,497
So get sensitivity readers, hire diverse people for your project.

310
00:14:06,497 --> 00:14:09,018
Video games can be fun and powerful.

311
00:14:09,018 --> 00:14:12,160
So I just really wanted to talk about this,

312
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:17,882
just using clothes as a means to really introduce your players or your fans

313
00:14:17,882 --> 00:14:22,704
to something new, to something way beyond what we can normally do.

314
00:14:23,975 --> 00:14:31,180
I really think that this makes a difference and I've seen a lot of things go wrong with it and

315
00:14:31,180 --> 00:14:36,984
that's why I think a great example of using fashion for cultural understanding is the Geeky Bayou Project.

316
00:14:36,984 --> 00:14:43,970
This artist, Karis Locke, has been reimagining Southeast Asian garment design for various

317
00:14:43,970 --> 00:14:48,133
movies and games. Her aim isn't to directly convert a character's

318
00:14:48,433 --> 00:14:51,313
clothing into local outfits, but to express their personality,

319
00:14:51,313 --> 00:14:54,694
their beliefs, and history using textiles, motifs,

320
00:14:54,694 --> 00:14:55,714
and silhouettes.

321
00:14:55,714 --> 00:14:58,735
She mentions that when the characters from existing

322
00:14:58,735 --> 00:15:01,216
sci-fi and fantasy tales are interpreted

323
00:15:01,216 --> 00:15:03,296
through garments from the other side of the world,

324
00:15:03,296 --> 00:15:05,577
issues of race and culture often emerge

325
00:15:05,577 --> 00:15:08,777
because the people creating them aren't from the culture.

326
00:15:08,777 --> 00:15:10,958
And these designs are not only fun,

327
00:15:10,958 --> 00:15:12,758
but they're a way to learn about the history

328
00:15:12,758 --> 00:15:16,039
behind traditional outfits, especially for Southeast Asia,

329
00:15:16,039 --> 00:15:18,320
in this case, which is often forgotten about.

330
00:15:19,201 --> 00:15:22,605
In this way, again, clothes are significant.

331
00:15:22,605 --> 00:15:23,867
And it's still video games.

332
00:15:23,867 --> 00:15:24,828
You can still have fun.

333
00:15:24,828 --> 00:15:27,932
You can still credit people and have fun with it.

334
00:15:27,932 --> 00:15:31,597
And you're allowed to learn things from other people.

335
00:15:31,597 --> 00:15:32,158
All right.

336
00:15:32,158 --> 00:15:33,240
So moving on.

